Text.Value: ...only to realise victory was never an option.
Draw your weapon.
This is the House of Hope. Where the tired come to rest, and the famished come to feed - lavishly.
The House of Hope. Where the tired come to rest, and the famished come to feed - lavishly.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He spreads his arms as he dramatically introduces this place.
EditorData.NodeContext: He spreads his arms as he dramatically introduces this place.
EditorData.SFXTags: Echoing voice to show size of Dining Hall

Text.Value: I don't care what you are - I care what you want.
Tut tut. No need for that crude cutlery of yours. As you can see, I'm amply provisioned.

EditorData.AnimationTags: CDavis: If not in the VO capture use point constructions
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He gestures across the table: plenty of silverware present.
EditorData.NodeContext: He gestures across the table: plenty of silverware present.

Text.Value: And you're in dire need. One skull, two tenants, and no solution in sight.
Hope. Hahaha! Such a tease.
What's better than a devil you don't know?
I'd rather die.
Not easily rattled, I see. Good. Makes the next part that much more straightforward.
Nice decor.
Why would you help me?
And so much more.

EditorData.AnimationTags: Clap from mocap needs to be cleaned

Text.Value: I need to think this over.
A devil you do.
Can you be more specific than 'somewhere'?
You do not seek it, but it has found you:
Are you not entertained? Well - far be it from me to disappoint.
Oh. That's disappointing. I prefer it when my clients put up a fight...
I'll have the last laugh in the end.
...it might just be your last.
Fair enough.
We're in the Hells, aren't we. Take me back. Now.
Take me back. Now.
I'll rip out your mocking tongue.
I never seek help from devils.
But the darkness won't save you anymore than the light could. You'll realise that in time.
Am I a friend? Potentially. An adversary? Conceivably. But a saviour? That's for certain.
Easy, easy. I'm here to help, not harm.

EditorData.NodeContext: Easy, easy: take your time - he's not intimidated, almost like he's talking to an excited child

Text.Value: I'm getting tired of your games.
Fuck. A cambion.

EditorData.NodeContext: Surprise, even fear in her voice. This is early in the game so she's still fresh from the hells. Referring to Raphael's first revelation of who he is.

Text.Value: I'll do anything to get rid of the tadpole.
Reach for your weapon.
Ah, yes. The tongue. Yet another piece of pleasurable anatomy you'll soon have to do without.
Your oath is in tatters, paladin. You abandoned your honour as soon as it became inconvenient.
And deny you the honour of my hospitality?
I could fix it all like that.

EditorData.AnimationTags: Clean up of fingers clicking CDavis: HUM_M_Rig_DFLT_CINE_FingerSnap_01
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He snaps his fingers on the word 'that'. As he does so, the candle flames suddenly shine unnaturally bright, bathing the scene in a hellish red glow.
EditorData.NodeContext: He snaps his fingers on the word 'that'. As he does so, the candle flames suddenly shine unnaturally bright, bathing the scene in a hellish red glow.

Text.Value: Level your weapon at the creature.
And what is madness but a denial of reality?
Call it a ninth sense.
Still, I've a feeling you'll change your mind. Before it's changed for you...
Consider your predicament.
I'll be there when it runs out.

EditorData.SFXTags: Sound of teleport at end of node exiting cinematic
EditorData.VFXTags: Teleport at end of cinematic back to bridge... will reuse previous FX

Text.Value: Take all the time you need - but make up your mind before you're counting down with tentacles.
I'll be around. Watching you squirm like a tadpole through a nice juicy brain.
Perhaps you haven't yet realised how desperate these times are. You will.
There. Middle-of-somewhere.

EditorData.VFXTags: Warped teleport effect to help sell idea of teleportation

Text.Value: I will rise as a kith'rak. Your threats do not worry me.
A rhetorical question, of course, but let me venture an answer.
You're mad if you think I'll make a deal with another devil.
You're mad if you think I'll make a deal with a devil.
Eloquent words, but I'm not seeking another pact.
Oh, a mere trifle. How dear is one's soul, really?
Take me back. After that, I never want to see you again.
It's worth very little with a tadpole in your head.
Hollering hells - you're a cambion.
I don't like this at all.

EditorData.NodeContext: This place is in the Hells, though Karlach doesn't realize that yet. She's put off but trying to stay cool.

Text.Value: Ignore him and fill your plate.
One might say you're a paragon of luck.
That's what separates us from the devils, soldier. They think our greatest strength is a weakness.

EditorData.NodeContext: Disgust with Raphael, but proud of being a hopeful mortal.

Text.Value: Everything is for sale. And you'd do well to sell while your stock has value - in desperate times, the price of honour plummets.
Try to cure yourself. Shop around - beg, borrow, and steal. Exhaust every possibility until none are left.
What makes you say that?
Then fix it - or die at my hand.

EditorData.SFXTags: sound for monitor transforming into Cambion
EditorData.StateChangeTags: Monitor needs to be replaced with Cambion from here on

Text.Value: Yes... I like it when my clients put up a fight...
All those pretty little symptoms - sundering skin, dissolving guts - they haven't manifested yet, have they?
My, aren't you a nervous one! I assure you I'm here to help, not harm.
Go on. Partake. Enjoy your supper. After all...
Come now. Why play hard to get when you're in deep over your tadpoled head?
Are these theatrics leading somewhere?
One skull, two tenants, and no solution in sight.
And if I do want to take this deal - how would I find you?
Because my compassion is boundless. I stride among the needy, giving comfort where I can.
What makes you think I need saving?
And when hope has been whittled down to the very marrow of despair - that's when you'll come knocking on my door.
I've always wondered what a laughing mind flayer sounds like.
By all means bite the hand that feeds you while you still have teeth.
I serve an oath, not a devil. My honour is not for sale.

Synopsis: The monitor has teleported you to a mysterious room and offered you dinner - and a deal.
